=== CKAN Provider ===

CKAN is an open source data management system. Each CKAN instance stores several CKAN data sets which may be grouped in CKAN groups and may be maintained by several CKAN organizations. For further information about CKAN please refer to: [http://ckan.org/ CKAN]. The CKAN provider stores meta information about CKAN data sets of a given CKAN group.

'''Note''': The referred CKAN instance must support CKAN API version 3. Otherwise, the CKAN Provider won't work.

<span style="color: red">The CKAN Provider is deactivated as of 7.0 by default. To activate, set <tt>com.fluidops.iwb.provider.CkanProvider=true</tt> inside ''providers.prop'' of your installation.</span>

==== Configuration Settings ====

{{#widget: com.fluidops.iwb.widget.DisplayConfigurationWidget
 | clazz = com.fluidops.iwb.provider.CkanProvider
}}

==== Example ====

On [[Admin:Providers]] add a new CKAN provider using a valid CKAN instance URL (e.g. ''<nowiki>http://datahub.io</nowiki>'') and a CKAN group name that exists within this instance (e.g. ''lodcloud'').

